<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-07-1258 </DOCNO><TEXT>Five cases of osteoid osteoma and five cases of osteoblastoma of the spineare reported. All the patients underwent was always histologically confirmed.Conventional radiographic technique using tomography constantly permittedthe diagnosis. Computed tomography was primarily useful for spatial localizationof the lesion. The authors evaluate the radiographic findings of thetwo lesions discussing the symptoms which are suspected for these pathologicconditions. Bone scintigraphy must precede radiological examination.</TEXT></DOC>